parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof can cause a loud noise, distraction, and potentially lead to accidents, especially if the driver is startled or loses control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The sunroof shatters suddenly
making a loud noise
and causing glass to fall into the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water entering the vehicle through the center console can cause electrical component failures, corrosion, and mold growth, leading to safety hazards and costly repairs.
symptoms: Water accumulates in the center console
flooding the interior of the vehicle
especially when the vehicle is stationary with the heat or air conditioning running.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DCM (Data Communication Module) computer can cause issues with vehicle communication systems, potentially leading to safety hazards, such as loss of critical vehicle functions or failure to alert the driver to important safety information.
symptoms: Not specified in the complaint
but potential symptoms may include issues with vehicle communication systems
such as Bluetooth connectivity
navigation
or warning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coils can cause the vehicle to fail to properly accelerate, leading to a loss of power and potentially increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to accelerate properly
the vehicle hesitates or stumbles when accelerating
the engine misfires or runs rough.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the adaptive cruise control system can cause the brake lights to not illuminate when the vehicle comes to a complete stop, potentially leading to rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The brake lights do not come on when the vehicle comes to a complete stop
the vehicle fails to maintain a safe distance from other vehicles
the vehicle fails to come to a complete stop in traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected explosion of the sunroof can cause shards of glass to fly into the vehicle, potentially causing injuries to occupants, and may also lead to accidents due to the sudden distraction.
symptoms: Loud explosion sound from above
followed by the sound of glass flying off from the vehicle
sunroof shattering without any apparent cause or warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration of the driver side mirror can cause distraction and obstruct the driver's view, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Driver side mirror shaking or vibrating when driving over 60mph.
